modules.description: This module provides bitwise operations for manipulating integer bitsets. It includes functions to count set bits (`popcnt`), find the number of leading zeros (`clz`), and trailing zeros (`ctz`). These operations are useful for low-level data processing, compression algorithms, and optimizing performance-critical code.

This module enables manipulation of character sets through operations like union, intersection, and difference, alongside element-wise transformations and membership checks. It operates on ordered sets of characters (represented as `Charset.t`) and individual characters (`Charset.elt`), supporting conversions to and from lists and sequences. Typical applications include text processing tasks requiring efficient set-based character analysis, such as validating character subsets, filtering specific symbols, or aggregating character ranges from sequential data sources.
